rComments: Highly recommend becoming friends with her as she is very kind, caring and gives great feedback! Genuinely cares about the content and her students. Highly recommend this prof!

I thought I would hate this class but with Stephanie as my prof it became my favorite class all semester. She wants you to do well, so her grading criteria is clear, just do the readings and pay attention in class and you will do well. She is a really nice person so I felt comfortable enough to ask her questions outside class. Highly recommend.

Very interesting class! The prof is super well informed and makes the material interesting and accessible. I loved her use of videos and artwork to reinforce the readings. She is really nice and easy to talk to outside of class. The final exam was long but it was a take-home so that is fair. Important to pay attention to lectures.

She is a good prof and she will be there for you if you don't understand something or have questions. Participation in class was apart of this course (wasn't a fan of that because I am shy) Also Take home exam was long af (still working on that) other than that a decent course.
Very interesting class. Awesome professor. Knows a ton about the subject - super smart. Easy to talk to outside class - super nice. Do the readings and pay attention in class and you will do fine.

She is an amazing professor! She acknowledges her own privilege and makes an effort to center the voices of Indigenous women. She is extremely knowledgable and constantly incorporates interesting material such as videos/guest speakers to keep the class interesting. Super nice and easy to talk to after class. Helpful feedback. She really cares...
